The paper deals with performance modeling of OFDMA/LTE networks, which is a subfield of network engineering. The paper specifically focuses on interference coordination, handover decisions, admission control, and proportional fair scheduling, which are all related to network infrastructure and performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also discusses SINR distribution and modulation and coding, which are related to information theory and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories. 

The paper also mentions ultra-dense deployments, which are related to distributed computing and parallel processing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible sub-category. 

Finally, the paper discusses interference modeling, which is related to systems and control. Therefore, cs.SI (Systems and Control) is also a possible sub-category.
